By utilizing the potential tersity of CJK characters in the language syntax, English-speaking programmers could make their programs much shorter wrt lines of code.<p>Because there's thousands of CJK characters to choose from, why not just use 印 instead of 印出 for 'print', or 如 instead of 如果 for 'if'? By using bracketing syntax instead of Python's indentation, we can cut down lines of code.<p>Here's your example using a terser style (the strings and comments would still be in English):<p>#!/usr/bin/env zhpy<p># 檔名: while.py<p>數= 23, 運= 真<p>當(運){<p><pre><code>  猜= 整(輸入'Enter an integer: ')

  如(猜 == 數){

    印'Congratulations, you guessed it.'

    運= 假 # this causes the while loop to stop

  }否如(猜<數) 印'No, it is higher than that.'

  否 印'No, it is lower than that.'
</code></pre>
}否 印'The while loop is over'<p>印'Done'
